00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:05.360
you have given a particular p
k a and a particular p h.

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:11.560
And so, if the p h is really
very far above the p k a, then

00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:13.920
you're going to be largely
depronated, and here's the

00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:16.800
math for these two numbers.

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:20.220
If you're at a p h that's really
below the p k a, then

00:04:20.220 --> 00:04:22.580
your molecules are going
to be pronated.

00:04:22.580 --> 00:04:24.920
And so, you're going to be
thinking about this kind of

00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:27.150
