00:04:28.220 --> 00:04:32.250
Biochemists spend a lot of time
thinking about the p k

00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:35.950
a's of amino acid side chains,
and there are often mechanisms

00:04:35.950 --> 00:04:38.810
that people propose of how an
enzyme works, and they're

00:04:38.810 --> 00:04:42.290
proposing that some residue is
going to play a role as a

00:04:42.290 --> 00:04:45.700
catalytic acid or a base
in an enzyme mechanism.

00:04:45.700 --> 00:04:49.300
And often people are proposing
